register_types.description: Register all types in the program

code_generator.description: Generate C code from the AST

typechecker.description:
Resolve and check types in the AST

This pass actually goes through the AST and checks the types of all the nodes.
Any remaining unresolved types should be resolved after this

namespace_dump.description: Dump the namespace tree for debug

reorder_structs.description:
Topologically sort structs

This is needed because in C structs need to be declared before they are used
in other structs. The ordered structs are stored in `program.ordered_structs`

compact_map.description:
An order-preserving hash map.

Uses open addressing with linear probing. Inspired by Python's dict.

buffer.description:
A growable buffer / string-builder type

The buffer is a growable array of bytes, with a null terminator at the end.
It can be used as a string builder, or as a string itself. It is also useful
to hold binary data.

map.description:
A simple hash-map

Preconditions:
- K must implement the `hash` method:    K::hash(this): u32
- K must implement the `eq` method:      K::eq(this, other: K): bool
